
 receive: receive (,  process) and store data.
 It uses different GNU libraries (see --info option)

 usage: ./receive -h -I
        ./receive -s 1024 -n 123 -X true -o samples/sample.png -p 1234

 version: v0.5.8d
          CImg_NetCDF.v0.8.3
 compilation date: (Feb  7 2020, 12:42:06)

    -o               samples/sample.cimg      output file name (e.g. "-o data.nc" or  "-o data.cimg -d 3" gives data_???.cimg)
    -r               results/sample.cimg      result file name (e.g. "-r result.nc" or  "-r result.cimg -d 3" gives result_???.cimg)
    -d               6                        number of digit for file names
    -s               1024                     size   of udp buffer
    -n               123                      number of vector
    -b               12                       size   of vector buffer (total size is b*s*4 Bytes)
    -c               2                        thread count (2 for receiving only or threads above 3 are processing one)
    -p               1234                     port where the packets are sent on the receiving device
    --CPU-factory    count                    CPU processing type, e.g. count or kernel
    --use-GPU        false                    show GUI (or -G option)
    --GPU-factory    program                  GPU processing type, e.g. program or function
    --do-check       false                    do data check, e.g. test pass (or -C option)
    --do-check-exit  false                    do data check exit on first error (or -E option)
    --do-warmup      false                    do data warmup, e.g. allocation and fill (or -W option)
    --help           true                     help (or -h option)
    --info           false                    show compilation options (or -I option)
    --version        false                    show version (or -v option)
